node.text: Omg y’all.....add this to the list of crazy things we used to do before Rona! This was exactly 1 year ago and little did I know I was documenting the very last time I went out grocery shopping with both kids 😂😂 Let’s just say I didn’t need a pandemic to tell me not to do that again!

node.text:
So I got up this morning to get the kids ready and realized I forgot to buy milk last night 😱 Then I remembered the instant porridges that the lovely team at @gracefoods gave to me and I thought well they can eat this! It was their first time trying it and they loved it! You know I always make porridge for them so if they liked this, then it must be really good! Definitely adding this to my list of quick breakfasts for those school mornings when I’m short on time! .

node.text:
Those Kids Can Cook‼️
My kids have been begging me to make their own cooking show and I finally caved! They made their own coconut drops and the shenanigans were never ending 😂 When you have kids with huge personalities everything is a comical adventure🤣 I’m also letting them explore in the kitchen and get comfortable with cooking. They provide the entertainment, and learn how to cook at the same time 🥰 Click the link in my bio for the full “Gregory & Aria cooking show” on my 🎥YouTube channel‼️
.
.
.

node.text:
@oceancoralspring in Falmouth gets a thumbs up from me. The staff is attentive, the grounds are beautiful, clean, and I chose this resort because they’re family friendly. There’s a kids water park on the resort in addition to a regular swimming pool, they have a Daisy Club where you can drop the kids off so that the adults can enjoy some adult time, there’s a bowling alley, a theatre, several restaurants to choose from, and the experience is top notch! I’ll be making a full blog post later on this week about my full review of the resort as well as details on my personal driver, and recommendations! Head to thatnursecooks.com and sign up to be notified as soon as the post goes live! 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text: Greg understood the assignment. Rarely am I left speechless but I was blown away at the amount of thought & preparation that went into making my day special. Surprise breakfast, suprise trip to Sharkies 😩 and a surprise dinner for two on the beach! Best birthday ever ❤️💛💚

node.text: Birthday girl 💚💛❤️ Greg planned the most epic birthday celebration for me yesterday. No time to make a post; I was really soaking up the moment and enjoying time with my family in the country I love so much. Cheers to more life!!!!! Thanks to everyone who reached out yesterday with the birthday love!!!! 🎂🎉

node.text:
Jerk bbq chicken is always a big flex! In these summer months sometimes turning on the stove is just too much for me 😩 My secret: a combo of @walkerswood jerk bbq sauce (approximately 1 cup), 2 tablespoons of mild jerk seasoning, and just a pinch of browning (it gives the best color) on the chicken. This sauce is also good on grilled vegetables as well so go ahead and get creative with it! Google: thatnursecancook jerk bbq chicken or jerk chicken for a lit recipe!
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Jollof Rice: A meal on its own ♥️

You def dont need no other body! 

Enjoy:
🍚
-1 red onion, chopped
-2 tbsp thyme
-1/2 tsp salt
-1/2 tsp all purpose seasoning
-1/2 chicken bouillon cube
-1 tsp curry powder
-3 bay leaves
-16 oz tomato pureé (sauce)
-6 oz tomato paste
-1/2 cup chicken stock
-2 1/2 cups parboiled rice
-1/2 cup water
.
.
.
.
